originalText.text:
Buyer beware! I have parked my motorcycle here countless times. At $25/day it's a great deal. Parked here last Friday and confirmed with the parking attendant the $25 rate since it's not posted. He said yes and I handed a healthy advance tip.

I come back Monday to pick up the bike and am charged $189 for 4 days - $40/day! I ask the manager what's up since he was there and he screams that the rate is posted (which it is not). Then he lies like a five year old that he "doesn't know how to change the rate in the system". He was there when I dropped the bike off and remembers.

Anyhow - no issue with the parking, just be warned about horrible business practices and dishonest staff.

originalText.text: Worst experience ever. Got there at the allocated exit timeslot and the car was already retrieved. All good. Then I asked the tenant if I could go and grab a bag from my apartment upstairs before taking the car and he said no problem. When I returned he charged me $45 extra for the 15min extra. Then grabbed my keys and said I will not get my car until I pay the additional amount. He got very aggressive very quickly, ending in me having to pay extra and having a terrible customer experience. Will never go back due to terrible attitude from garage attendant.
